<i>Now's my chance to leave.</i>

12:19.791 --> 12:21.257
No, I'll wait five more seconds

12:21.259 --> 12:22.675
<i>so I don't seem too eager.</i>

12:22.677 --> 12:23.643
<i>Four...</i>

12:23.645 --> 12:24.677
<i>three...</i>

12:24.679 --> 12:25.812
<i>two...</i>

12:25.814 --> 12:27.730
Well, thanks for keeping
our daughter company.

12:27.732 --> 12:29.132
Man, she can be
a real drag, huh?

12:29.134 --> 12:32.318
We're gonna go have
a little fun. See ya!

12:33.571 --> 12:34.904
(laughing)

12:34.906 --> 12:37.657
You're on fire tonight, bro.

12:38.742 --> 12:41.027
But, Lily, being a judge
is my dream job.

12:41.029 --> 12:42.529
DAPHNE'S VOICE:
So your dream job

12:42.531 --> 12:44.114
is more important
than my dream job?

12:44.116 --> 12:46.116
Exactly.
Now you're getting it.

12:46.118 --> 12:47.534
(clucks tongue)
Nope.

12:47.536 --> 12:48.551
Start over.

12:48.553 --> 12:50.036
So your dream job's

12:50.038 --> 12:51.838
more important
than my dream job?

12:51.840 --> 12:54.541
But, baby, you already have
the best job in the world:

12:54.543 --> 12:56.009
Mom.
Nope.

12:56.011 --> 12:57.076
Start over.

12:57.078 --> 12:58.962
So your dream job's
more important

12:58.964 --> 13:00.096
than my dream job?

13:00.098 --> 13:03.166
Hey, I gave up peeing
in the shower for you.

13:03.168 --> 13:04.184
Nope.

13:04.186 --> 13:05.218
Start over.

13:05.220 --> 13:06.553
So your dream job's

13:06.555 --> 13:08.388
more important
than my dream job?

13:08.390 --> 13:09.505
Of course not.

13:09.507 --> 13:10.740
But this isn't

13:10.742 --> 13:12.475
just about our future.

13:12.477 --> 13:14.060
It's about everyone's.

13:14.062 --> 13:15.061
As a lawyer,

13:15.063 --> 13:16.729
I couldn't stop big oil
from polluting,

13:16.731 --> 13:18.231
but as a judge...

13:18.233 --> 13:19.482
well, maybe I can.

13:19.484 --> 13:21.284
And that's why I took the job.

13:22.019 --> 13:23.186
You've just been "convincered."

13:23.188 --> 13:24.487
Wait.

13:24.489 --> 13:26.372
You already took the job?

13:26.374 --> 13:28.158
Without even talking
to your wife?

13:28.160 --> 13:29.859
Start over.

13:29.861 --> 13:31.244
Start over... start over.

13:31.246 --> 13:33.213
What the damn hell?!

13:34.748 --> 13:36.299
Hi, Reverend
Lowell?

13:36.301 --> 13:38.301
Whew.
Made it through my half.

13:38.303 --> 13:39.869
You're up.

13:39.871 --> 13:41.054
Oh. Uh...

13:41.056 --> 13:43.289
The-the truth is,
we-we have

13:43.291 --> 13:45.141
a complicated,
messy history

13:45.143 --> 13:46.726
that-that we're
not too proud of.

13:46.728 --> 13:48.011
But...

13:48.013 --> 13:49.345
we're sorry
that we lied,

13:49.347 --> 13:52.999
and hope that
you can forgive us.

13:55.936 --> 13:57.904
Nope, I can't do it.

13:57.906 --> 13:59.939
You're going to have
to find a new officiant.

13:59.941 --> 14:01.224
Okay.

14:01.226 --> 14:02.325
Well, these
things happen.

14:02.327 --> 14:03.359
And a new church.

14:03.361 --> 14:05.828
What the damn hell?!

14:06.780 --> 14:09.749
TED: <i>This evening could not</i>
<i>get any worse.</i>

14:09.751 --> 14:11.618
Whenever you're ready.
Crap!

14:13.721 --> 14:14.871
Hey, Ted.

14:14.873 --> 14:16.589
Thanks for
being so great.

14:16.591 --> 14:18.608
I'm lucky to have you
around this weekend.

14:18.610 --> 14:20.593
Ooh, yeah...

14:20.595 --> 14:22.095
About that...

14:22.097 --> 14:25.014
I should really go see
about the, uh...

14:25.016 --> 14:26.883
So, sex?
My room is very close.

14:26.885 --> 14:28.635
(Cassie laughs)

14:28.637 --> 14:29.903
TED:
Sophia. Hi.

14:29.905 --> 14:31.221
Oh, God. Wesley.

14:31.223 --> 14:33.523
Wait. Wait, you're Wesley?

14:33.525 --> 14:35.058
Hey, Cassie.
(laughs nervously)

14:35.060 --> 14:37.260
Your parents were just saying
you have a new boyfriend.

14:37.262 --> 14:39.646
"Boyfriend" is
a little premature.

14:39.648 --> 14:40.980
Though I did
pay for dinner.

14:40.982 --> 14:43.432
Ted and I are
very happy.

14:43.434 --> 14:44.784
Are we?

14:44.786 --> 14:48.071
(crying): Even if... he'll
never replace you.

14:48.073 --> 14:50.456
(sobbing)

14:52.509 --> 14:53.826
So, Sophia. Hi.

14:53.828 --> 14:54.844
I'm Ted.

14:54.846 --> 14:56.713
Robin's friend.

14:56.715 --> 14:58.447
What do you say we give
these two old flames

14:58.449 --> 15:00.383
a chance to...
catch up alone,

15:00.385 --> 15:01.968
and maybe you and I
could go get a drink.

15:01.970 --> 15:03.386
Are you hitting on me?
Dude!

15:03.388 --> 15:04.671
Ted, let's go!

15:08.642 --> 15:10.877
You tip...

15:10.879 --> 15:12.061
(scoffs)

15:12.063 --> 15:13.680
...poorly.

15:17.704 --> 15:20.012
Look, I know. I shouldn't
have taken the job

15:20.013 --> 15:21.095
without telling Lily.

15:21.097 --> 15:22.847
Why are you so ticked off
about it?

15:22.849 --> 15:25.016
Because I know
what she's going through.

15:25.018 --> 15:26.067
I always dreamed

15:26.069 --> 15:28.620
of having a career
I could be proud of,

15:28.622 --> 15:30.705
but my husband never
supported me.

15:30.707 --> 15:31.890
Eventually,

15:31.892 --> 15:34.676
I had to... make a choice.

15:34.678 --> 15:35.743
Now, every day,

15:35.745 --> 15:36.961
I'm out there,

15:36.963 --> 15:39.130
I'm fighting for the good guys,
and I love it.

15:39.132 --> 15:40.398
Doesn't

15:40.400 --> 15:41.916
your wife deserve th, too?

15:41.918 --> 15:46.004
Wow. Um, maybe
you're right.

15:46.006 --> 15:49.340
I didn't realize how many
sacrifices you'd made.

15:50.359 --> 15:51.976
What is it you do, anyway?

15:51.978 --> 15:53.761
I'm a lobbyist
for a big oil company.

15:53.763 --> 15:55.379
What the damn hell?!

15:57.382 --> 15:58.733
You know
that I'm an environmentalist!

15:58.735 --> 16:00.384
That's why you don't want me
to become a judge.

16:00.386 --> 16:02.219
But you're the reason
I <i>have</i> to become a judge!

16:02.221 --> 16:04.689
You're the devil incarnate!
And outcarnate!

16:04.691 --> 16:06.891
Every kind of carnate!

16:08.460 --> 16:09.644
Please, is-is there

16:09.646 --> 16:10.878
any way you'd reconsider?

16:10.880 --> 16:12.580
No! No, no!

16:12.582 --> 16:14.749
You two are both
terrible people.

16:14.751 --> 16:17.819
Who found each other
in this crazy world!

16:17.821 --> 16:19.170
Aw!

16:19.172 --> 16:21.739
And who lie
about <i>how</i> they found each other.

16:21.741 --> 16:23.958
So, please leave now. Just...

16:23.960 --> 16:26.044
Ugh! Ugh!

16:26.046 --> 16:28.346
You know what?
You're right.

16:28.348 --> 16:30.748
We shouldn't have lied
about our story.

16:31.433 --> 16:32.850
I <i>love</i> our story.

16:32.852 --> 16:34.802
Sure, it's messy,
but it's the story

16:34.804 --> 16:37.188
that got us here,
about to get married.

16:37.190 --> 16:39.524
I love it, too.

16:39.526 --> 16:41.492
Every messy chapter.

16:41.494 --> 16:43.978
I love that you slept
with over 250 women

16:43.980 --> 16:46.114
before deciding that
I was your favorite.

16:46.116 --> 16:47.282
This is killing me.

16:47.284 --> 16:48.833
And I love
that we just had

16:48.835 --> 16:50.434
to keep having sex
with each other,

16:50.436 --> 16:51.903
even when we were dating
other people.

16:51.905 --> 16:53.437
This is <i>really</i> killing me.

16:53.439 --> 16:55.106
And I love that your
marriage proposal

16:55.108 --> 16:57.208
involved a strip
club, lying to me,

16:57.210 --> 17:01.095
and pretending to bang the
woman I <i>hate</i> for two months.

17:01.097 --> 17:02.664
I love that we keep
a running tally

17:02.666 --> 17:04.248
of all the different rooms
we've had sex in.

17:04.250 --> 17:07.502
I love that two weeks ago, we
put this room on that list.

17:07.503 --> 17:09.420
Huh? Come on, Rev.

17:09.422 --> 17:11.622
That's got to be worth
some kind of reaction, right?

17:11.624 --> 17:13.858
I mean, right where
your hymnal is, is where we...

17:13.859 --> 17:16.010
we...

17:17.896 --> 17:20.064
(laughs)

